have no noticeable impact, at the current level of accuracy, on\nthe structural parameters derived by asteroseismology. Conclusions. The stellar\nmodels presently used to carry out quantitative seismic analyses of sdB stars\nare reliable for the task. The stellar parameters inferred by this technique,\nat least for those that could be tested (M*, R*, and log g), appear to be both\nvery precise and accurate, as no significant systematic effect has been found.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 14 Mar 2013 07:38:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-15"}
