h a population of different heating amplitudes can\nroughly reproduce the observations. (b) We also consider a loop model with\nsteady heating and non-uniform cross-section of the loop along its length, and\nfind that this model can also reproduce the observed DEMs, provided the loop\nexpansion factor $\\gamma \\sim$ 5 - 10. More observational constraints are\nrequired to better understand the nature of coronal heating in the short\nemerging loops on the quiet Sun.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 14 Mar 2013 12:32:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-04-15"}
